    "note": "This is a first-pass screening tool, not a performance-suitability determination. The PACCAR FOM confirms no static minimum runway length exists -- length/width/weight performance is a function of the day's weight, weather, and conditions and belongs in ForeFlight, not in a static per-airport screen. The only static, condition-independent screening fact kept here is hard-surface + weight-bearing class. Both airframes are dual-wheel gear, so the gate reads NASR's DW (dual-wheel) weight-bearing column only -- never SW/DTW/DDTW -- and compares it against the airframe's lightest landing weight as the floor a runway must clear.",
